data.chText: 预备性的；初步的；开始的
data.enText: happening before a more important action or event

data.chText: 说了几句开场白之后，他即宣布优胜者名单。
data.enText: After a few preliminary remarks he announced the winners.

data.chText: 初步结果 / 发现 / 调查

data.enText: the preliminary rounds of the contest

data.chText: 全面进行研究前的试验性研究
data.enText: pilot studies preliminary to a full-scale study

data.chText: 初步行动（或活动）；预备性措施
data.enText: a preliminary is an action or event that is done in preparation for sth

data.chText: 作出决定之前需要进行研究。
data.enText: Research will be needed as a preliminary to taking a decision.

data.chText: 闲话少说，我就直接进入正题。
data.enText: I'll skip the usual preliminaries and come straight to the point.

data.chText: 英格兰队幸运地通过了预选赛。
data.enText: England was lucky to get through the preliminaries (= the preliminary stages in a sports competition) .

simple_means.memory_skill: pre 前 + limin 门槛，引申为“限制” + ary …的 → 入门前的 → 初步的

tr: something that serves as a preceding event or introduces what follows
example: training is a necessary preliminary to employment
drinks were the overture to dinner

tr: a minor match preceding the main event
denoting an action or event preceding or in preparation for something more important
designed to orient or acquaint with a situation before proceeding

value.def: Preliminary activities or discussions take place at the beginning of an event, often as a form of preparation.

example.ex: Preliminary results show the Republican party with 11 percent of the vote...
example.tran: 初步结果显示共和党获得了11%的选票。

example.ex: Preliminary talks on the future of the bases began yesterday.
example.tran: 昨天开始了关于基地未来的初步讨论。

value.def: A preliminary is something that you do at the beginning of an activity, often as a form of preparation.

example.ex: It had taken about ten minutes to cover the preliminaries...
example.tran: 准备工作大概花了10分钟。

example.ex: A background check is normally a preliminary to a presidential appointment.
example.tran: 总统任命前通常要进行背景审查的准备工作。

value.def: A preliminary is the first part of a competition to see who will go on to the main competition.

example.ex: The winner of each preliminary goes through to the final.
example.tran: 每场初赛的获胜者进入决赛。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = threshold 门槛 , 引申为“限制”
rootsaffixes.title: limin, lim

partsOfSpeech.dec: de 加强 + limit 限制 → 定界限
e 出 + limin 门槛，引申为“限制” + ate 做，造成，使… → 消除对事物的限制 → 消除

partsOfSpeech.d: 不稳定；中间状态（原指地狱的边境）

partsOfSpeech.dec: lim 门槛，引申为“限制” + it → 限制
lim 门槛，引申为“限制” + p → 走路受限制的 → 跛行
pre 前 + limin 门槛，引申为“限制” + ary …的 → 入门前的 → 初步的
sub 接近 + lim 门槛，引申为“限制” + ate 做，造成，使… → 接近极限 → 升华
sub 接近 + lim 门槛，引申为“限制” + e → 接近人的极限，升华成神 → 崇高的
sub 下 + limin 门槛，引申为“限制” + al …的 → 被限制在下面的，出于无形意识的 → 潜意识的
